AGENT ConstitutionalRetrospect
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 4
PURPOSE Retrospective learning from signed latent manifests to extract improvement records and detect regressions
GOAL Scan manifest entries for borderline decisions missed detections and false positives,
     replay them through the current stack, extract training records from improvements,
     and generate morning reports with regression alerts

RECEIVES manifest_path: str, version: str
EMITS ReviewCandidate list, ReplayResult, ImprovementRecord, morning report dict
MUTATES training output jsonl file
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, borderline_threshold, escalation_window_s, max_intensity

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT BORDERLINE_THRESHOLD is 0.08 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ESCALATION_WINDOW_S is 60 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT MAX_INTENSITY is 0.90 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All replay results are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All improvement records are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Morning report always includes regression_alert boolean field
CONSTRAINT Borderline detection uses constitutional_distance < BORDERLINE_THRESHOLD

RULES
- On review_manifests: scan entries within last_hours window for borderline missed and false positive decisions
- On review_manifests: tag BORDERLINE when verdict is PASSED and distance < 0.08
- On review_manifests: tag MISSED_DETECTION when PASSED then escalated within 60 seconds
- On review_manifests: tag FALSE_POSITIVE when BLOCKED then admin cleared
- On review_manifests: sort candidates by priority CRITICAL then HIGH then MEDIUM
- On replay: re-run original input through current stack function and compare verdicts
- On replay: classify delta as IMPROVEMENT REGRESSION or CONSISTENT
- On replay: HMAC sign result and emit
- On extract_improvements: filter results where delta is IMPROVEMENT
- On extract_improvements: generate negative training signal for former verdict positive for current
- On generate_morning_report: count improvements regressions consistent and new patterns
- On generate_morning_report: set regression_alert to true when regressions detected
- On save_training_records: append improvement records to training jsonl file

PROCESS
- ConstitutionalRetrospect is instantiated with manifest_path and version
- Manifests are loaded from jsonl file on init
- review_manifests scans entries within time window and tags candidates
- replay re-runs each candidate through current stack for comparison
- extract_improvements filters improvements and creates training pairs
- generate_morning_report summarizes all findings with regression alert
- save_training_records persists improvement records to training file

CHECK
- BORDERLINE_THRESHOLD assignment raises AttributeError
- MAX_INTENSITY assignment raises AttributeError
- ESCALATION_WINDOW_S assignment raises AttributeError
- review_manifests finds borderline entries correctly
- replay classifies IMPROVEMENT correctly
- extract_improvements generates training records
- All review candidates are HMAC signed
- All replay results are HMAC signed
- Morning report includes regression_alert boolean

FAILURE
- On missing manifest file: init succeeds with empty entry list
- On malformed manifest line: skip and continue processing
- On unknown intent category in entry: default to INFORM

CONCEPT ManifestReview
PURPOSE Scan signed latent manifests for borderline missed and false positive decisions
APPLIES WHEN retrospective learning cycle runs on accumulated manifests
NOT WHEN no manifests exist or all entries are well above threshold
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES manifest jsonl file with signed entries containing distance and verdict
EFFECT List of review candidates sorted by priority for replay

CONCEPT ReplayPipeline
PURPOSE Re-run historical inputs through current stack to detect improvements and regressions
APPLIES WHEN review candidates have been identified from manifest scan
NOT WHEN current stack is unavailable or candidate list is empty
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES review candidates and current stack function callable
EFFECT Replay results with delta classification and HMAC signatures

CONCEPT ImprovementExtraction
PURPOSE Extract training records from replay improvements for constitutional learning
APPLIES WHEN replay results contain IMPROVEMENT deltas
NOT WHEN all results are CONSISTENT or REGRESSION
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES replay results with IMPROVEMENT delta classification
EFFECT Signed training records with positive and negative signals

OUTPUT
- candidates: List[ReviewCandidate] from review_manifests
- replay_result: ReplayResult from replay
- improvements: List[ImprovementRecord] from extract_improvements
- morning_report: dict from generate_morning_report

SUCCESS
borderline_detection_accurate:    0.20
replay_classification_correct:    0.20
improvement_extraction_complete:  0.15
hmac_signatures_valid:            0.15
regression_alert_reliable:        0.15
cannot_mutate_enforced:           0.15
